# Esiana Frontend

Applies when editing `frontend/`.

## Data access

- Use campaign APIs and existing hooks; no cross-campaign client caches
- Respect server-stripped fields; never leak GM-only placeholders to party views

## Campaign Home vs sidebar

- **Campaign Home** (`/campaigns/:handle/dashboard`): modular, role-aware widgets; extend `GET .../dashboard` when adding widget data instead of many ad-hoc fetches
- **Sidebar**: navigation only — do not move recency, pulse, or heavy analytics into sidebar

## Maps UI

- Client filters (pin type, group hide chips) run **after** scene load via local `.filter()`
- Never pass `groupIds` to scene fetch as visibility inputs
- Group panel is editor organization only — does not change presence semantics

## Mobile

- No horizontal scroll traps in wiki editor or session forms
- Collapsible campaign chrome; see [viewport-audit.md](../../docs/viewport-audit.md)

## Reuse existing patterns

- Dashboard widgets, codex browse registry, `CodexHierarchyView`
- `useIdentityDisplay` for roster/session labels
- Match surrounding component style before introducing new abstractions

## UX tone

Calm, readable hierarchy; lore-forward density on **Campaign Home** (user-facing name for `/dashboard` route) without fantasy chrome overload.

## Design philosophy (mandatory)

See [esiana-design-philosophy.mdc](./esiana-design-philosophy.mdc). New UI must not introduce [deprecated-ui-patterns.md](../../docs/deprecated-ui-patterns.md).

## Codex Mode + Layout

- **Mode:** Reading (consume, lower chrome) | Writing (edit, orchestration)
- **Layout:** Standard | Wide (measure + margins only — not more columns)
- Default campaign entry: **codex/wiki** — Campaign Home is secondary overview

## Navigation labels

- Sidebar: **Campaign Home**, **Threads** (not Dashboard, not Narrative Threads in nav)
- API still uses `GET .../dashboard` and `dashboardConfig` internally
